✅ LCD Display with I2C – External Notes
🔷 1. Introduction
An I2C LCD is a regular 16x2 or 20x4 LCD attached to an I2C interface module (PCF8574).

It reduces the number of Arduino pins used from 6 to just 2: SDA and SCL.

Common I2C addresses: 0x27 or 0x3F.

🔷 2. Components Required
Component	Quantity
Arduino UNO/Nano/Mega	1
I2C LCD 16x2 Display	1
Jumper Wires	4
Breadboard (optional)	1

🔷 3. Circuit Connections
I2C LCD Pin	Arduino UNO	Description
GND	GND	Ground
VCC	5V	Power supply
SDA	A4	I2C Data line
SCL	A5	I2C Clock line

📝 Note: On Mega → SDA = pin 20, SCL = pin 21. On ESP32/ESP8266, it varies.
code:
#include <Wire.h>
#include <LiquidCrystal_I2C.h>
LiquidCrystal_I2C lcd(0x27,16,2);

void setup() {
lcd.init();
lcd.backlight();
lcd.home();

}

void loop() {
  lcd.setCursor(0,0);
  lcd.print("hello");

}
